I do have an issue with the mayor,

1012
01:26:39,258 --> 01:26:47,980
negotiating mitigation, a mayor that's going to be leaving in a couple of months, and the project doesn't start until 2017.

1013
01:26:48,460 --> 01:26:57,561
And the next mayor come this January might have very different ideas on mitigation and what they may want to do to Winthrop Street and some of the areas that are impacted.

1014
01:26:58,241 --> 01:27:08,183
And, you know, I'm not quite sure why the mitigation, although I think it's warranted, has to be discussed with this current mayor at this particular point.

1015
01:27:08,933 --> 01:27:22,779
And, you know, I'm not sure how other councilors feel, but I truly think this should be an issue that is confronted with the next mayor and their vision and their ideas that they have, Mr. President.

1016
01:27:23,039 --> 01:27:27,201
And on that note, I'd just like to thank Eversource again for appearing.

1017
01:27:28,041 --> 01:27:28,341
Thank you.

1018
01:27:28,361 --> 01:27:29,222
Thank you, Councilor Mox.

1019
01:27:29,622 --> 01:27:31,743
Chair recognizes Vice President Longo Kern.

1020
01:27:32,243 --> 01:27:33,804
Thank you, President DelaRusso.

1021
01:27:34,922 --> 01:27:44,314
My questions were mainly answered, but with regards to the excavation and then the backfill, how long of a stretch will you be doing before you then go and repave the street?

1022
01:27:46,737 --> 01:27:51,442
How much trench are we going to have open in the 3.2 miles in Medford at a time?

1023
01:27:51,583 --> 01:27:52,964
That's kind of my question.

1024
01:27:55,126 --> 01:28:01,408
And I appreciate the frustration of this answer, but we have not yet developed a construction schedule and a construction management plans.

1025
01:28:01,448 --> 01:28:04,850
We are still in what we call the plan project phase.

1026
01:28:05,190 --> 01:28:07,791
So all of that will be discovered at some point.

1027
01:28:07,851 --> 01:28:08,751
We're not there yet.

1028
01:28:08,931 --> 01:28:10,572
However, typically what I will say is

1029
01:28:12,630 --> 01:28:16,712
The trenching crews make an average, as Bill said, about 100 to 150 feet a day.

1030
01:28:17,472 --> 01:28:19,413
That's the forward progress they make.

1031
01:28:20,214 --> 01:28:24,616
And that involves a linear, continuous process.

1032
01:28:24,656 --> 01:28:31,039
The front of this train, if you will, they are saw cutting, they are removing material.

1033
01:28:31,499 --> 01:28:33,460
The middle of the train is then coming in and

1034
01:28:34,520 --> 01:28:42,861
putting in forms and putting in the pipe work and then behind that comes the concrete fill work and then the pavement after that.

1035
01:28:44,082 --> 01:29:02,067
How much of that, generally, we do want to keep it in line with the progress, but at the same time, if we can get in and get out faster, if it makes sense to, you know, say, start the saw cutting now while we're still finishing up the pavement, because perhaps it's before a holiday weekend, we may extend that.

1036
01:29:02,427 --> 01:29:04,788
You know, all those considerations come into account.

1037
01:29:05,828 --> 01:29:07,329
All that to say, there's not a formula.

1038
01:29:07,909 --> 01:29:11,710
It really does depend on the area in question and the timing of where we're at.

1039
01:29:12,132 --> 01:29:17,076
Okay, so you don't cut up the 100, 150 feet a day and then fill it the next day.

1040
01:29:17,096 --> 01:29:20,319
It could be, you know, you could go a couple times.

1041
01:29:20,439 --> 01:29:22,220
We would close it every night.

1042
01:29:22,541 --> 01:29:23,682
It would never be left open.

1043
01:29:23,902 --> 01:29:30,187
We would have it plated every night so that there would always be access when we're not working that for that 150 feet.

1044
01:29:30,787 --> 01:29:33,790
And we hear you loud and clear that this is a concern of yours.

1045
01:29:34,290 --> 01:29:37,552
and we will certainly factor this into our scheduling.

1046
01:29:38,032 --> 01:29:48,198
We understand that there is a fatigue on construction and we would like to try to mitigate that impact on the residents of Medford.

1047
01:29:48,238 --> 01:30:00,285
And my second point, I agree with Councillor Knight with regards to a traffic light study and then my suggestion obviously was going to be a traffic impact study, but can you go into a little

1048
01:30:00,766 --> 01:30:11,469
more detail with regards to the traffic impact study that will be done beforehand so that we make sure there's, you know, least disturbance to the already enough traffic that we already have.

1049
01:30:11,849 --> 01:30:19,351
Because we're talking about some of the highly congested areas of Mystic Ave, Main Street, South Street, Winthrop Street.

1050
01:30:19,411 --> 01:30:21,552
Those are some of the busiest streets.

1051
01:30:21,612 --> 01:30:26,473
I mean, in the morning, Councilman Locke mentioned, you can't get through Medford Square to the high schools.

1052
01:30:27,169 --> 01:30:33,914
is a mess, Mystic Ave leading into Somerville, McGrath Highway is always backed up, so it would be nice if...

1053
01:30:35,188 --> 01:30:39,071
detailed studies were done to create as least impact as possible.

1054
01:30:39,511 --> 01:30:44,874
We are bringing in a professional traffic management engineering firm.

1055
01:30:46,235 --> 01:30:50,658
This is what they specialize in, or one of the fields they specialize in.

1056
01:30:50,678 --> 01:30:51,478
They will be coming in.

1057
01:30:51,498 --> 01:30:55,981
They will be looking at each municipality, at each area where the project goes through.

1058
01:30:57,162 --> 01:30:59,604
They might do actual traffic count measurements.

1059
01:30:59,644 --> 01:31:01,405
That's yet to be determined how their approach

1060
01:31:01,918 --> 01:31:06,922
And how they'll do that, they would come back with recommendations after studying the areas.

1061
01:31:07,843 --> 01:31:11,826
Essentially, how can we build this project with the least amount of traffic impact?

1062
01:31:11,886 --> 01:31:15,069
That is the task they are charged with providing to us.

1063
01:31:15,629 --> 01:31:21,234
That, to get to that final product, they would make, you would do research with the municipalities.

1064
01:31:21,274 --> 01:31:22,755
They'd bring back recommendations to us.

1065
01:31:23,175 --> 01:31:27,699
We would bring back preliminary conclusions to the municipalities, again,

1066
01:31:28,364 --> 01:31:36,446
whether it be to councils or whether it be to engineering departments, get the input, get the local knowledge that our engineers may not have from you.

1067
01:31:37,267 --> 01:31:38,887
That gets incorporated into the plan.

1068
01:31:39,727 --> 01:31:40,027
Thank you.

1069
01:31:40,068 --> 01:31:46,589
And then this council has discussed hiring a traffic engineer within our engineering department.

1070
01:31:47,130 --> 01:31:54,672
So you'll be given recommendations, but will you also furnish the results of the studies to the engineering department?

1071
01:31:54,692 --> 01:31:54,872
Yes.

1072
01:31:56,068 --> 01:32:11,531
make that part of the committee report that any traffic studies that are done by this professional management firm, any results along with the recommendations be furnished to our engineering department for any future help that it could give past this project.

1073
01:32:11,551 --> 01:32:15,291
I think that would be helpful because I do see something like that in the future.

1074
01:32:16,172 --> 01:32:19,352
And the traffic management plans would be approved by the city.

1075
01:32:19,492 --> 01:32:21,452
I mean, we wouldn't be doing this on our own.

1076
01:32:21,673 --> 01:32:24,293
We would be looking for city approval.

1077
01:32:25,387 --> 01:32:26,647
I thank you very much for coming.

1078
01:32:26,667 --> 01:32:31,428
I hope that we can maybe get another update in six months so that we can keep on top of the project.

1079
01:32:31,728 --> 01:32:36,309
We're getting calls all the time when people start hearing about this street's getting dug up again.

1080
01:32:36,409 --> 01:32:41,510
So I thank you for coming, and I appreciate the slideshow that you've provided us.

1081
01:32:42,130 --> 01:32:43,891
It's helpful to stay on top of it.

1082
01:32:46,791 --> 01:32:47,991
Thank you, Madam Vice President.

1083
01:32:48,051 --> 01:32:49,752
Chair recognizes Councilor Carviello.

1084
01:32:50,132 --> 01:32:50,912
Thank you, Mr. President.

1085
01:32:52,807 --> 01:33:09,015
As you know, we have a growing bicycle community, and I would hope that you would reach out to that committee, the Bicycle Advisory Committee, and discuss with them, because I'm sure you'll be taking over some of the new bike paths, bike lanes that have just been put in.

1086
01:33:10,015 --> 01:33:12,477
So if you could reach out to that group.

1087
01:33:17,339 --> 01:33:21,441
Because some of the streets you're going down are where the mayor has put the new bike lanes.

1088
01:33:23,497 --> 01:33:27,518
If there's a contact, if you could provide it to us, we will reach out to them.

1089
01:33:27,778 --> 01:33:28,438
Okay.

1090
01:33:28,598 --> 01:33:30,079
I will give the contact person your name.

1091
01:33:30,339 --> 01:33:30,599
Okay.

1092
01:33:30,799 --> 01:33:31,059
Thank you.

1093
01:33:33,059 --> 01:33:33,359
Thank you.

1094
01:33:33,379 --> 01:33:49,903
So on the, uh, motion of council night as amended by, uh, council Longo Kern, uh, to receive this paper and to, uh, act on those items that were requested and that we can also, uh,

1095
01:33:50,528 --> 01:34:07,917
schedule with you folks a follow-up meeting in the next term in six months or so so that we can be updated and the citizens can be updated and also hopefully we can do a better job at announcing the meeting so that more citizens can be present.

1096
01:34:08,477 --> 01:34:11,458
And in the interim, if there's any concerns, please contact us.

1097
01:34:11,618 --> 01:34:20,442
You know, we are available and we're happy to, to engage and try to find answers or address any concerns that need to do with that.

1098
01:34:20,922 --> 01:34:22,563
This has been very helpful for all of us.

1099
01:34:23,023 --> 01:34:28,386
And for the same sense, I think there's one citizen that wants to speak on this before you adjourned this matter.

1100
01:34:28,406 --> 01:34:31,287
If you'd like to please state your name and address for the record.

1101
01:34:31,637 --> 01:34:32,657
My name is Michael Ruggiero.

1102
01:34:32,957 --> 01:34:34,998
I live on 18 Pembroke Street.

1103
01:34:35,178 --> 01:34:36,918
I'm an intervener in this project.

1104
01:34:37,539 --> 01:34:42,080
And there's a couple of things I want to say before I move on to some other points.

1105
01:34:42,660 --> 01:34:45,381
The first is the general tone of this conversation.

1106
01:34:45,421 --> 01:34:47,201
This project has not been approved yet.

1107
01:34:47,721 --> 01:34:51,482
And I think that's important that we consider the pros and cons of this project.

1108
01:34:52,463 --> 01:34:59,225
The gentleman from Eversource mentioned that there would be significant rate improvements as a result of this project.

1109
01:35:00,995 --> 01:35:03,077
There are no guarantees to rate payers.

1110
01:35:03,277 --> 01:35:11,785
As of right now, this project is roughly slated to be about $74 million, and those $74 million will come directly out of our pockets.

1111
01:35:12,666 --> 01:35:21,094
I want to read a prepared statement I have about this issue in particular, because I think it's important that I make sure I say all the things that I want to.

1112
01:35:23,669 --> 01:35:33,331
At City Hall on July 15th, Eversource presented its plan for an 8-mile, $74 million power line, which they hope to build underground along Main Street and Route 38.

1113
01:35:34,611 --> 01:35:40,893
Many citizens from Medford, myself included, voiced their objections to this initial power line presentation.

1114
01:35:41,493 --> 01:35:43,353
There's a couple of points I want to bring up here.

1115
01:35:43,913 --> 01:35:47,654
Unfortunately, while I really appreciate Eversource coming down, there

1116
01:35:48,248 --> 01:35:54,353
And all the questions that the citizens of Medford asked at July 15th have not been addressed.

1117
01:35:54,793 --> 01:36:00,618
There were about five major flavors of questions, and I'm just going to go through them one by one.

1118
01:36:02,380 --> 01:36:14,930
While Eversource's power line improvement is intended to benefit the citizens of greater Boston, it's really opaque to understand exactly how Medford will receive any improvements whatsoever.

1119
01:36:16,070 --> 01:36:18,753
I think that this was a major theme throughout the night.

1120
01:36:18,833 --> 01:36:26,800
Why is Medford going to be shouldering the responsibility if much of this Power Live improvement is greater New England?

1121
01:36:27,000 --> 01:36:30,243
That's a very vague term of what's going to be improved.

1122
01:36:30,283 --> 01:36:35,308
So I think there needs to be a point-by-point analysis on why Medford needs this plan.

1123
01:36:36,689 --> 01:36:41,333
The $74 million price tag will be covered by rate payers.

1124
01:36:41,902 --> 01:36:45,644
And it's disappointing that this price tag has not been included in this presentation.

1125
01:36:46,765 --> 01:36:53,349
Understandably, they didn't want to perhaps spook people, but I think it's an important element knowing that we're going to be paying for this.

1126
01:36:54,309 --> 01:37:02,914
And as was mentioned at the conversation, there was a lot of concerns about traffic and environmental impact.

1127
01:37:03,295 --> 01:37:07,037
And unfortunately, while once again, you know, I understand you all are very busy,

1128
01:37:07,532 --> 01:37:12,795
it would have been good to actually see more information about what is the environmental impact of this.

1129
01:37:12,915 --> 01:37:14,215
It's going to have an impact.

1130
01:37:14,615 --> 01:37:21,479
Now, I'm sure Eversource will do the best it can to minimize that impact, but it will have an impact on our roads and our environment.

1131
01:37:21,939 --> 01:37:23,740
So how is that going to be mitigated?

1132
01:37:24,200 --> 01:37:30,403
Currently, there is a multi-prong evidentiary process that's going on right now.

1133
01:37:30,954 --> 01:37:35,797
Currently there's 28 pages of unanswered questions that various citizens have asked.

1134
01:37:36,657 --> 01:37:44,922
The city of Somerville is in fact an intervener on the process, not an intervener, they're a step below intervener, but they're engaging in this process.

1135
01:37:45,102 --> 01:37:48,924
I would encourage everyone on this council to engage with it more as well.

1136
01:37:49,004 --> 01:37:55,748
If you would like to view the 28 pages of questions or any of the documents that I have access to being an intervener in this project,

1137
01:37:56,216 --> 01:37:57,596
please call me at any time.

1138
01:37:57,657 --> 01:38:01,638
I'm more than happy to furnish that information, as I'm sure Eversource is as well.

1139
01:38:04,059 --> 01:38:06,900
At the meeting, I asked four main questions.

1140
01:38:07,640 --> 01:38:17,923
And one of the big questions I would like to hear answered, and it's in this 28 pages of questions that Eversource has to respond to, is basically, why is this necessary?

1141
01:38:18,243 --> 01:38:22,665
With improvements in alternative energy sources, from solar to wind,

1142
01:38:23,199 --> 01:38:25,800
Why is it that we need to build basically another pipeline?

1143
01:38:25,840 --> 01:38:26,761
Because that's what this is.

1144
01:38:27,201 --> 01:38:28,141
It's a pipeline.

1145
01:38:28,181 --> 01:38:30,202
Now, of course, electricity is going through it.

1146
01:38:30,662 --> 01:38:31,763
But are there other options?

1147
01:38:32,463 --> 01:38:35,484
I'm sure Eversource will do the best they can answering their questions.

1148
01:38:35,905 --> 01:38:40,247
Currently, the way I stand on this whole process is I'm not really sure.

1149
01:38:40,707 --> 01:38:42,247
Maybe it is the best thing for Medford.

1150
01:38:42,608 --> 01:38:43,308
Maybe it's not.

1151
01:38:43,828 --> 01:38:50,091
But they are required by law to provide an alternative strategy for this process.

1152
01:38:50,151 --> 01:38:52,492
Now, Eversource, as of right now, have provided

1153
01:38:53,071 --> 01:39:01,877
an alternative pipeline, another much longer road that would tear up many more streets than the current preferred plan.

1154
01:39:02,778 --> 01:39:04,799
But this is sort of a false choice.

1155
01:39:04,879 --> 01:39:09,803
It's like going to a diner and there's two choices on the menu, scrambled eggs or eggs sunny side up.

1156
01:39:10,143 --> 01:39:11,164
It's still eggs, right?

1157
01:39:11,644 --> 01:39:17,428
So what I really hope to see from Eversource is why other options will not solve these problems.

1158
01:39:17,809 --> 01:39:22,452
And as of right now, I mean, because they're working with the interveners to answer these questions,

1159
01:39:22,815 --> 01:39:24,836
They haven't presented many of these answers yet.

1160
01:39:25,336 --> 01:39:30,979
So I think it's important that we remind ourselves that this is a big project, and it is not finalized yet.

1161
01:39:31,639 --> 01:39:34,080
Eversource has many different hurdles to overcome.

1162
01:39:34,620 --> 01:39:35,801
But here's what we do know.

1163
01:39:36,261 --> 01:39:38,362
The process will be expensive.

1164
01:39:38,922 --> 01:39:40,943
It will have an impact on our society.

1165
01:39:41,544 --> 01:39:46,486
I would encourage everyone to think seriously about this process that's going to cost us

1166
01:39:46,973 --> 01:39:47,353
in the end.

1167
01:39:47,453 --> 01:39:56,337
Now, maybe, as the gentleman said, this is part of another sort of project that will help New England immensely.

1168
01:39:56,777 --> 01:40:00,118
But I think we need to consider these ramifications very seriously.

1169
01:40:00,518 --> 01:40:12,363
If anyone at home is interested in receiving any of the documents I have mentioned, please call me any time at 844-TAKE-GVT.

1170
01:40:12,763 --> 01:40:15,804
Thank you very much for allowing me to speak, and thank you very much for Eversource for coming down.

1171
01:40:17,783 --> 01:40:25,230
Sure, my number, once again, is 844-TAKE-GVT.

1172
01:40:25,950 --> 01:40:28,052
So, TAKE-GVT.

1173
01:40:28,152 --> 01:40:34,538
Please, I'm more than happy, you can also email me anytime at mr.takegovernment.com.

1174
01:40:34,658 --> 01:40:38,602
I have access to hundreds of pages of documents, and I'm slowly sort of filtering my way through.

1175
01:40:39,795 --> 01:40:51,624
I would also encourage any electrical engineer... Can the public also be assured that these documents are available through public means, through the commission that oversees utilities as well?

1176
01:40:52,445 --> 01:40:56,808
I'll post them on my website, takegovernment.com, in the next couple of days with the campaign.

1177
01:40:56,828 --> 01:40:58,229
It's been a little hectic.

1178
01:40:58,489 --> 01:40:59,110
Thank you, everyone.

